The paper proposes a deep neural network for texture-related applications, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The network architecture and feature representation are based on multi-level pooling, which is a common approach in deep learning for image analysis and classification tasks. The paper also discusses the impact of feature fusion and compares the proposed method with state-of-the-art texture descriptors, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and information retrieval (cs.IR) research areas.
